Long story short is I have no fight this coming weekend. Instead of packing for my flight I spent the weekend coaching and keeping my mind off of the fact that my camp wouldn’t end in the @bellatormma cage like I had planned. I had an amazing camp and tremendous improvements but with my previous opponents mishap, and it being impossible to secure a new one on short notice for this coming card, had to call it off. Live to fight another day. Can’t wait to get in there next year, happy I was able to spend my weekend coaching my students and watching them continue to succeed. Thank you to everyone who had their hands in my camp, benefits will be reaped soon enough. See y’all on @showtime in 2023

Quick side note from my fight coming up to talk about this last weekends state championships. I’m so incredibly proud of every kids performance. Everyone emptied the tank, and every kid from districts to regions to state worked their ass off to make it. 17 qualifiers, more than any team in the state boys and girls combined. 8 medalists, with 2 state finalists that are the embodiment of the hardest worker in the room reaching the highest point they could. 11 kids in the top 10, and 20 in the top 20. I know some of them aren’t as satisfied with their results as others but they should know that I am so tremendously proud of their work and all they have just begun to accomplish. They are rowdy and loud, a giant mess, wildly dysfunctional and I couldn’t be happier to be represented by them. Team work makes the dream work, and I can’t wait for this post season. Would’ve taken third in the state as a team with the team points we racked up, and third most medalists in all of the state behind the two 6A powerhouses. Congratulations to all your hard work kids. Now tell your friends, your team mates, it’s time to get back in the gym. Your week of rest is over, the grind continues. Next season starts today. LFG.

A highlight reel knockout and epic comeback all rolled into one. Lucas Brennan, that was insane! 

📺 Watch the #Bellator298 @MonsterEnergy Prelims LIVE on YouTube.

👊 @lucasbrennanmma reacts to his comeback win! A humble assessment from the rising star of Bellator. 

#Bellator298

How do I even put last night into words, so much happening but also quite indescribable. My opponent and I put on a fight of the night, and my body is sure feeling it today. Even when not a strike is being thrown, there is so much happening behind either of our eyes. Picking up an exhausting amount of data, trying to find safe ways to engage with one another, both of us very methodical in our attempts to execute the plan. Almeida fought an amazing fight, he was an extremely respectful and game opponent and I’m honored to have shared the cage with him. He is a problem for anyone he faces, and easily one of the happiest and most humble fighters I’ve ever interacted with. Last night was a huge blend of happiness and relief, with disappointment in my performance and so many mixed emotions. I am extremely happy to have come away with the win, with lots of notes to take back home with me. Thank you to my opponent, thank you to my team, thank you to my coaches, and to my sponsors. I couldn’t do it without my support system. And if I’m gonna be testing my chin again, I’m gonna need you all. Thank you @bellatormma as always, I’ll be seeing you again. On to the next one. Skywalker stock is on the rise again. LFG. NG FTW.

Last time I posted this room was about a year and a half ago give or take. Had 800 records and just over a hundred books. 1300 records, maybe somewhere north of 400 books of various purposes, 100+ CDs, dozen sweet watches, handful of cassettes, tons and tons of art pieces, collectibles, figures and everything inbetween. A lot of the set up is still the same as it was last time I made this, just way more depth to it now. More material to ingest. Keeping all my playlists tangible and on hand, spotify wrapped around every inch of the room lol. Never ending project. So much to show, so little time. Check it all out and enjoy your stay🫶🏼
